  "issue_title": "beta: invest in harness reliability (mock voice cycle, CI matrix, sqlite test isolation)",
  "issue_body": "## Motivation\n\nThe codebase has 380+ unit tests but the harness around real voice flows is still thin: integration paths depend on subprocesses (`arecord`, `sox`, `deep-filter`, `whisper-server`, `piper`, `aplay`) that aren't easily mocked, on Jetson-only hardware (LyraT I2S, ALSA APE card), and on long-running services (`whisper-server`, `llama-server`). The result is that:\n\n- Pre-existing `tools::parser` test fails on macOS because `Memory available:` only matches Linux `free` output.\n- `memory::tests::promotion_redacts_person_memory_in_namespace_note` fails intermittently under parallel tests (sqlite contention).\n- Real voice cycles can only be validated on the Jetson, by a human, by ear. The recent #14 / #15 chase needed 6+ deploy-test rounds because there was no way to repro the bug on the build host.\n\nFor beta we want a reliable harness that catches regressions before hardware deploy.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n- **Mock voice cycle harness.** A test that exercises `voice_loop::voice_cycle()` end-to-end with mock implementations of: arecord (returns a pre-recorded WAV), DFN/sox (passthrough), whisper-server (HTTP mock returning canned transcripts), llama (LlmClient::Mock), piper+aplay (writes PCM to a buffer instead of speaker). Verifies the orchestration, error paths, and timing.\n- **Deterministic STT/LLM mocks.** Test doubles for `SttEngine` and `LlmClient` that can be configured per-test (\"on cycle 2, return text X\").\n- **Platform gating.** Mark tests that hit external commands or Linux-specific syscalls with `#[cfg(target_os = \"linux\")]` or `#[ignore]` + a CI matrix that runs them on Linux. macOS dev box runs the rest.\n- **Parallel-safe sqlite tests.** All `memory::*` tests serialize on a process-wide mutex or use isolated tempfile DBs, so `cargo test --lib` is deterministic.\n- **CI matrix.** `.github/workflows/ci.yml` runs `cargo check`, `cargo test --lib`, `cargo clippy --deny warnings` on both Linux and macOS targets. Optional: cross-compile genie-core for aarch64 to catch deploy regressions early.\n- **Harness coverage report.** `cargo llvm-cov` or `tarpaulin` baseline in CI; surface uncovered orchestration code.\n\n### Out of scope\n- Hardware-in-the-loop testing (genuine Jetson + LyraT). Tracked separately if needed.\n- Whisper/Piper model fidelity testing. The harness assumes those subprocesses behave per their docs.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- `cargo test -p genie-core --lib` is 100% green on both macOS and Linux without `--ignored`.\n- A new `tests/voice_loop_integration.rs` (or similar) exercises one full mocked voice cycle and asserts on transcript flow, conversation store, and audit logs.\n- CI runs on every PR.\n- The two failing tests called out above (`tools::parser` Memory-available, `memory::promotion_redacts_person_memory`) are fixed (the test, not the production code).\n\n## Related\n\n- #14, #15 \u2014 bugs that would have been caught by a mocked voice-cycle harness without 6+ Jetson deploy rounds.\n",
